headline: Management and Program Analyst at U.S. Immigration and Customs Enforcement (ICE)

defaultPosition.description: Provide timely and accurate updates to ICE property databases and reports to assist in the informed decision-making process as it pertains to ICE property and fleet matters.  Respond to Help Desk Remedy tickets within an expedited time-frame on unresolved issues pertaining to program issues and conduct follow-up status within one business day. Create and implement plans to improve the vehicle data quality systems which requires accurate analysis to assist in informed decision-making processes to the ICE Fleet management.  Serves as subject-matter expert of Fleet Reports of Survey policy-related questions and best practices by answering all subject-related questions within a 24-hour period.  Resolves customer issues as required. Perform data research to enhance system processes.
